Class Crow

java.lang.Object
com.example.projectfx.species.Species
com.example.projectfx.species.Omnivore
com.example.projectfx.species.Crow
All Implemented Interfaces:
Movable, Reproducible, Sleepable
public class Crow extends Omnivore
The Crow class represents a crow species, which is an omnivore, capable of eating both fruits and other species. It extends the Omnivore class and includes specific behaviors for moving, eating, reproducing, and sleeping.

    • eat

      public void eat(Object food)
      The crow eats the specified food, which can be fruits or other species. If the food is a fruit, it consumes it and gains energy. If the food is a species, it attacks and consumes the species, gaining its energy.
      Overrides:
      eat in class Omnivore
      Parameters:
      food - The food the crow consumes, which can be either fruits or a species.

    • reproduce

      public void reproduce()
      The crow reproduces if the number of crows is sufficient. The total number of crows increases by one upon successful reproduction.
      Specified by:
      reproduce in interface Reproducible
      Specified by:
      reproduce in class Omnivore
